article_title: Auto Makers Report Strong U.S. October Sales
article_text:
Low fuel prices propped up demand for trucks and sport-utility vehicles in the U.S., boosting October auto-sales growth to a decade-high pace.

U.S. auto sales rose 6.1% to 1.28 million units in October, according to Autodata Corp. October’s pace of sales, if it were the same over the entire year, would equate to 16.46 million units in 2014—indicating the American car business is poised to post its best performance since before the...

twitter.description: Auto makers continued to post strong sales in the U.S., as low fuel prices—propping up demand for trucks and SUVs—boosted October’s sales growth rate to a decade-high pace during a month that has traditionally been a slow period for the industry.
